feat: company follows + in-app notifications

Adds a "follow company" feature with in-app notifications for four
trigger types:
  - article_mention  - company tagged on a published article
  - financials_new   - new fiscal year landed in company_financials cache
  - roles_changed    - BRREG roles changed (board, daily leader, etc.)
  - status_changed   - bankruptcy / liquidation / deletion transitions

## Data model
- company_follows: which user follows which orgnr
- notifications: per-user feed of events (RLS: row owner only)
- company_roles_cache: BRREG roles snapshot used to diff weekly
- company_status_cache: BRREG status snapshot used to diff weekly

## Database triggers
- After insert on article_company_tags: fan out to all followers
  when the article is already published
- After update on articles.published_at (NULL -> not NULL): fan out
  for every existing tag on the article (covers the "tag-then-publish"
  flow that the previous trigger would miss)

## Edge function changes
- brreg-proxy: new action=status (status flags from enheter endpoint)
- refresh-financials-cache: insert financials_new notifications when
  a year is genuinely new for a followed orgnr
- suggest-companies: BRREG-matches each AI-suggested name and returns
  { name, orgnr } where confident, falls back to null otherwise.
  Backward-compatible: still accepts string[] in the UI normalizer
- refresh-roles-and-status: new fn that diffs cached roles/status
  against fresh BRREG data, inserts notifications on transitions

## Cron
- New weekly job 'refresh-roles-and-status-weekly' (Mon 04:00 UTC)
- Uses same pg_net pattern as the existing monthly financials cron

## UI
- FollowCompanyButton: gjenbrukbar toggle. Optimistic, auth-aware,
  hidden when logged out
- CompanyDetail: button placed alongside "Legg til i liste"
- NotificationBell: header bell with unread count, dropdown listing
  the latest 10, Realtime-subscribed to INSERTs and UPDATEs
- /varsler: dedicated page with filter pills per type, "mark all as
  read", pagination of 30 per page, Realtime for new arrivals
- Profile: new "Følger" tab between "Grupper" and "Innstillinger"
  with list of followed companies and per-row unfollow
- ArticleEditor: AI suggestions now carry orgnr - clicking a tag
  becomes an instant add when AI matched, falls back to manual
  BRREG lookup when orgnr is null

## Routes
- App.tsx: /varsler added for Vite fallback
- src/app/varsler/: Next.js page + _loader + client following the
  existing pattern (page.tsx + ssr:false dynamic)

## Notifications schema
- type: 'article_mention' | 'financials_new' | 'roles_changed' | 'status_changed'
- payload: { article_id, title } | { year, omsetning, ... } |
           { added, removed } | { konkurs, konkursdato, ... }

## RLS
- company_follows: owner can SELECT/INSERT/DELETE own rows
- notifications: owner can SELECT and UPDATE (mark as read);
  inserts only via service_role / db triggers
- caches: public SELECT, writes only via service_role

